SDLC Overview

Planning - During the planning stage, me and mustafa were able to find a problem concerning the student healthcare services in the universities. Most of the students have to spend most of their time waiting to access the campus clinics to get medical consultations. In order to to manage we had to come up with a prototype of an online system of booking clinic appointments. The project is connected with Sustainable Development Goal 3 that is aimed to enhance the access to healthcare services. The step involved in this stage was establishing the concept of the project, project goals and developing a product vision which solves the problem

Analysis - During the analysis stage we obtained system requirements and the key system users. Students, doctors, and clinic staff were identified as the actors. Key system functions include user login, booking appointments, selecting available doctors, viewing appointment schedules, and cancelling appointments, and according to this a use case diagram is formed shown before

Design - During the design stage we were concerned with coming up with the design of the system and the interface. sketches were done in order to show how the application looks and the user flow. The layout consisted of pages that were the login page, appointment booking page, doctor availability page, and page of appointments management. This phase was aimed at making the system simple, easy to use and navigate by the students who must make medical appointment within a short time.

Prototype Development - The prototype development process involved us in creating theclinic appointment booking system prototype in our working application. The prototype provides an overview of the functionality of the system. such as user registration, booking of appointments, choosing the doctors and managing the appointments. Project files, as well as monitoring the progress of development, were saved in Github. The repository was sorted into separate folders which contained the materials of various stages of the Software Development Life Cycle like planning, design, testing and final product prototype.

Testing - During the testing stage, the team tested the functions and usability of the prototype. The test plan was developed to test some significant features like login, booking of appointments and cancelling of appointments. To test the prototype under real user interaction, I Mustafa tested the prototype with Arifa. The ease of use, interface design and system functionality as a whole were measured in regards to feedback. Improvements within the system were found based on the feedback obtained to improve it overall




